{'brief': 'strong, mighty, powerful', 'long': 'strong (originally and generally of physical strength); mighty, powerful, vehement, sure.'}
{'brief': 'powerful, able, possible', 'long': '(a) of persons: powerful, able, (b) of things: possible.'}
{'brief': 'dominion, strength, power', 'long': 'dominion, strength, power; a mighty deed.'}
{'brief': 'strong, mighty, powerful', 'long': 'strong (originally and generally of physical strength); mighty, powerful, vehement, sure.'}
{'brief': 'might, power, marvelous works', 'long': '(a) physical power, force, might, ability, efficacy, energy, meaning (b) plur: powerful deeds, deeds showing (physical) power, marvelous works.'}
{'brief': 'strong, powerful', 'long': 'strong, powerful, mighty.'}
{'brief': 'large, great', 'long': 'large, great, in the widest sense.'}
{'brief': 'I think, judge, observe', 'long': '(a) I think, (b) I think, judge, (c) I direct the mind to, seek for, (d) I observe, (e) I care for.'}
{'brief': 'understanding, intellect, mind', 'long': 'understanding, intellect, mind, insight.'}
{'brief': 'I am sober-minded, exercise self-control', 'long': 'I am of sound mind, am sober-minded, exercise self-control.'}
{'brief': 'the mind, reasoning faculty', 'long': 'the mind, the reason, the reasoning faculty, intellect.'}
{'brief': 'thought, purpose', 'long': 'thought, purpose, aspirations.'}
{'brief': 'the mind, intellect', 'long': 'the mind, intellect, thought, understanding.'}
{'brief': 'a thought, design, the mind', 'long': 'a thought, purpose, design; the mind; the heart, soul, feelings.'}
{'brief': 'double-minded, wavering', 'long': '(lit: of two souls, of two selves), double-minded, wavering.'}
{'brief': 'I am calm, vigilant, sober', 'long': '(lit: I am sober), I am calm (vigilant), circumspect.'}
{'brief': 'thought, intention, purpose', 'long': 'thinking, consideration; a thought, purpose, design, intention.'}
{'brief': 'opinion, counsel, judgment, intention', 'long': 'opinion, counsel, judgment, intention, decree.'}
{'brief': 'I mock', 'long': 'I mock, ridicule.'}
{'brief': 'I lay my hands upon, slay, kill', 'long': 'I lay my hands upon, and so: I slay, kill.'}
{'brief': 'I mock, scoff', 'long': 'I mock, scoff, jest, jeer.'}
{'brief': 'I sneer at, disdain', 'long': '(properly: I turn up the nose as a sign of contempt), I sneer at, disdain.'}
{'brief': 'I make a public show of', 'long': 'I make a public show of, expose to public shame.'}
{'brief': 'mockery', 'long': 'mockery, scoffing, scorn.'}
{'brief': 'a mocker', 'long': 'a mocker, scoffer.'}
{'brief': 'lamentation, wailing', 'long': 'lamentation, wailing, mourning, sorrow.'}
{'brief': 'I mourn, lament', 'long': 'I mourn, lament, feel guilt.'}
{'brief': 'I cut off, mourn', 'long': '(a) I cut, cut off, strike, smite, (b) mid: I beat my breast or head in lamentation, lament, mourn, sometimes with acc. of person whose loss is mourned.'}
{'brief': 'mourning, sorrow', 'long': 'mourning, sorrow, sadness, grief.'}
{'brief': 'I exceed, am left over', 'long': '(a) intrans: I exceed the ordinary (the necessary), abound, overflow; am left over, (b) trans: I cause to abound.'}
{'brief': 'I increase, multiply', 'long': 'I increase, multiply.'}
{'brief': 'I abound, increase', 'long': 'I have more than enough; I abound, increase.'}

{'brief': 'anything hidden, a mystery', 'long': 'a mystery, secret, of which initiation is necessary; in the NT: the counsels of God, once hidden but now revealed in the Gospel or some fact thereof; the Christian revelation generally; particular truths or details of the Christian revelation.'}
{'brief': 'a race, people, the Gentiles', 'long': 'a race, people, nation; the nations, heathen world, Gentiles.'}
{'brief': 'near, nearby, a neighbor', 'long': 'near, nearby, a neighbor.'}
{'brief': 'a neighbor', 'long': 'a neighbor.'}
{'brief': 'another, different', 'long': "(a) of two: another, a second, (b) other, different, (c) one's neighbor."}
{'brief': 'an oath', 'long': 'an oath.'}
{'brief': 'I swear, take an oath', 'long': 'I swear, take an oath, promise with an oath.'}
{'brief': 'I curse, invoke curses', 'long': 'I curse, invoke curses, devote to destruction.'}
{'brief': 'a curse, a cursed thing', 'long': 'a votive offering, a thing devoted to God; a curse, the thing cursed.'}
{'brief': 'the taking of an oath, an oath', 'long': 'the taking of an oath, an oath.'}
{'brief': 'I listen, obey', 'long': 'I listen, hearken to, obey, answer.'}
{'brief': 'I keep, guard, observe', 'long': 'I keep, guard, observe, watch over.'}
{'brief': 'I lay hold of, obtain', 'long': 'I am strong, mighty, hence: I rule, am master, prevail; I obtain, take hold of; I hold, hold fast.'}
{'brief': 'I keep, guard, observe', 'long': '(a) I guard, protect; mid: I am on my guard, (b) act. and mid. of customs and regulations: I keep, observe.'}
{'brief': 'I hold fast, bind, restrain', 'long': '(a) I hold fast, bind, arrest, (b) I take possession of, lay hold of, (c) I hold back, detain, restrain, (d) I hold a ship, keep its head.'}
{'brief': 'I obey one in authority', 'long': 'I obey one in authority, conform to advice, obey, follow.'}
{'brief': 'listening to, obedient', 'long': 'listening to, obedient, submissive.'}
{'brief': 'I persuade, urge', 'long': 'I persuade, urge.'}
{'brief': 'obedience', 'long': 'obedience, submissiveness, compliance.'}
{'brief': 'olive oil', 'long': 'olive oil, oil.'}
{'brief': 'anointing-oil, ointment', 'long': 'anointing-oil, ointment.'}
{'brief': 'an olive tree', 'long': 'an olive tree; the Mount of Olives.'}
{'brief': 'Olive-grove, Olive-yard, the mount Olivet', 'long': 'Olive-grove, Olive-yard, the mount Olivet.'}
{'brief': 'a wild olive tree', 'long': 'a wild olive tree, oleaster.'}
{'brief': 'a cultivated olive tree', 'long': 'a cultivated olive tree.'}
{'brief': 'highest, most high, the heights', 'long': 'highest, most high, the heights.'}
{'brief': 'height, heaven', 'long': 'height, heaven; dignity, eminence.'}
{'brief': 'I ill-treat', 'long': 'I exhaust by labor or suffering, wear out, overpower, oppress.'}
{'brief': 'affliction, ill-treatment', 'long': 'affliction, ill-treatment, oppression, misery.'}
{'brief': 'I overpower, quell, treat harshly', 'long': 'I overpower, quell, treat harshly.'}
{'brief': 'I make narrow, persecute, press hard', 'long': '(a) I make narrow (strictly: by pressure); I press upon, (b) I persecute, press hard.'}

{'brief': 'I fit together, prepare', 'long': '(a) I fit (join) together; met: I compact together, (b) act. and mid: I prepare, perfect, for his (its) full destination or use, bring into its proper condition (whether for the first time, or after a lapse).'}
{'brief': 'I give orders to, prescribe', 'long': 'I give orders to, prescribe, arrange.'}
{'brief': 'ordaining, ordinance, disposition', 'long': 'ordaining, ordinance, disposition.'}
{'brief': 'I set, establish, appoint, conduct', 'long': 'I set down, bring down to a place; I set in order, appoint, make, constitute.'}
{'brief': 'pagan, heathen, gentile; a Gentile, non-Jew', 'long': 'pagan, heathen, gentile; subst: a Gentile, non-Jew.'}
{'brief': 'I suffer long, have patience, am forbearing', 'long': 'I suffer long, have patience, am forbearing, perseverance.'}
{'brief': 'patience, forbearance', 'long': 'patience, forbearance, longsuffering.'}
{'brief': 'enduring evil, patient of evil', 'long': 'enduring evil, patient of evil, patiently forbearing.'}
{'brief': 'peace, peace of mind', 'long': 'peace, peace of mind; invocation of peace a common Jewish farewell, in the Hebraistic sense of the health (welfare) of an individual.'}
{'brief': 'I am peaceful, keep the peace, am at peace', 'long': 'I am peaceful, keep the peace, am at peace.'}
{'brief': 'I make peace, reconcile', 'long': 'I make peace, reconcile.'}
{'brief': 'quiet, tranquil', 'long': 'quiet, tranquil, peaceful.'}
{'brief': 'not quarrelsome, peaceable', 'long': 'peaceable, abstaining from fighting, not contentious.'}
{'brief': 'peaceable, disposed to peace', 'long': 'peaceable, disposed to peace, profitable.'}
{'brief': 'a people, the crowd', 'long': "(a) a people, characteristically of God's chosen people, first the Jews, then the Christians, (b) sometimes, but rarely, the people, the crowd."}
{'brief': 'a crowd', 'long': 'a crowd, mob, the common people.'}
{'brief': 'the people, multitude, rabble', 'long': 'properly: the people, especially citizens of a Greek city in popular assembly, but in NT, multitude, rabble.'}
{'brief': 'perfect, full-grown', 'long': 'perfect, (a) complete in all its parts, (b) full grown, of full age, (c) specially of the completeness of Christian character.'}

{'brief': 'I complete, accomplish, make perfect', 'long': '(a) as a course, a race, or the like: I complete, finish (b) as of time or prediction: I accomplish, (c) I make perfect; pass: I am perfected.'}
{'brief': 'I end, accomplish, pay', 'long': '(a) I end, finish, (b) I fulfill, accomplish, (c) I pay.'}
{'brief': 'perfectness, perfection', 'long': 'perfectness, perfection, maturity.'}
{'brief': 'completion, fulfillment, perfection', 'long': 'completion, fulfillment, perfection.'}
{'brief': 'perfect, full-grown', 'long': 'perfect, (a) complete in all its parts, (b) full grown, of full age, (c) specially of the completeness of Christian character.'}
{'brief': 'a perfecter, completer', 'long': 'a perfecter, completer, finisher.'}
{'brief': 'I pursue, persecute', 'long': 'I pursue, hence: I persecute.'}
{'brief': 'persecution', 'long': 'chase, pursuit; persecution.'}
{'brief': 'a persecutor', 'long': 'a persecutor.'}
{'brief': 'crooked, perverse, unfair', 'long': 'crooked, perverse, unfair, curved, tortuous.'}
{'brief': 'improper, unrighteous, perverse', 'long': '(lit: out of place, unusual, unbecoming), improper, unrighteous, perverse.'}
{'brief': 'I turn, change, corrupt, pervert', 'long': 'I turn, change, corrupt, pervert.'}
{'brief': 'I change for the worse, corrupt, pervert', 'long': 'I change for the worse, corrupt, pervert.'}
{'brief': 'swine', 'long': 'a swine, hog, sow.'}
{'brief': 'a hog, boar, or sow', 'long': 'a hog, boar, or sow.'}
{'brief': 'a pit, ditch', 'long': 'a pit, ditch.'}
{'brief': 'a pit, well', 'long': 'a pit, well, cistern.'}
{'brief': 'I have in full, am far, it is enough', 'long': 'I have in full, am far, it is enough.'}
{'brief': 'I am, exist, am in possession', 'long': 'I begin, am, exist, am in possession.'}
{'brief': 'a field, property', 'long': 'a piece of landed property, a field; plur: possessions, property, possibly landed property, property in land.'}

{'brief': 'a vessel to contain liquid, utensil, tackle', 'long': 'a vessel to contain liquid; a vessel of mercy or wrath; any instrument by which anything is done; a household utensil; of ships: tackle.'}
{'brief': 'a possession', 'long': 'a possession, holding fast.'}
{'brief': 'obtaining, possessing, possession', 'long': 'acquiring, obtaining, possessing, possession, ownership.'}
{'brief': 'I win, get, buy, possess', 'long': '(a) I acquire, win, get, purchase, buy, (b) I possess, win mastery over.'}
{'brief': 'goods, substance, property', 'long': 'goods, substance, property, possessions.'}

{'brief': 'I consent fully, confess', 'long': '(a) I consent fully, agree out and out, (b) I confess, admit, acknowledge (cf. the early Hellenistic sense of the middle: I acknowledge a debt), (c) I give thanks, praise.'}
{'brief': 'praise', 'long': 'praise.'}
{'brief': 'I praise', 'long': 'I praise.'}
{'brief': 'I praise, commend', 'long': 'I praise, commend, applaud.'}
{'brief': 'commendation, praise', 'long': 'commendation, praise, approval.'}
{'brief': 'praise', 'long': 'praise, commendation.'}
{'brief': 'I proclaim, herald, preach', 'long': 'I proclaim, herald, preach.'}
{'brief': 'a proclamation, preaching', 'long': 'a proclamation, preaching.'}
{'brief': 'I declare openly, preach', 'long': 'I declare openly, proclaim, preach, laud, celebrate.'}
{'brief': 'I preach beforehand', 'long': 'I announce or preach beforehand, announce by herald.'}

{'brief': 'I bring good news, preach good tidings', 'long': 'I bring good news, preach good tidings, with or without an object, expressing either the persons who receive the good news or the good news itself (the good news being sometimes expressed as a person).'}
{'brief': 'I announce publicly, proclaim', 'long': 'I announce publicly, proclaim.'}
{'brief': 'of great value', 'long': 'of great value, very costly, very precious.'}
{'brief': 'of great price, precious, honored', 'long': 'of great price, precious, honored.'}
{'brief': 'precious, honored, honorable', 'long': '(held precious, hence) precious, honored, honorable in rank.'}
{'brief': 'a price, honor', 'long': 'a price, honor.'}
{'brief': 'very costly, very precious', 'long': 'very costly, very precious, of great value.'}
{'brief': 'equally privileged, equal', 'long': 'equally privileged, equal in honor.'}
{'brief': 'preciousness, costliness', 'long': 'preciousness, costliness, worth.'}
{'brief': 'a watching, guard, prison, imprisonment', 'long': 'a watching, keeping guard; a guard, prison; imprisonment.'}
{'brief': 'a prison', 'long': 'a prison.'}
{'brief': 'one bound, a prisoner', 'long': 'one bound, a prisoner.'}
{'brief': 'a keeper of a prison, a jailer', 'long': 'a keeper of a prison, a jailer.'}
{'brief': 'a prisoner, captive', 'long': 'a prisoner, captive.'}
{'brief': 'I enclose, shut in', 'long': 'I enclose, shut in, make subject to.'}
{'brief': 'a fellow captive', 'long': 'a fellow captive or prisoner.'}
{'brief': 'I profane', 'long': 'I profane, pollute, violate.'}
{'brief': 'profane, secular, unspiritual, godless, worldly', 'long': 'permitted to be trodden, accessible.'}
{'brief': 'I collect, am profitable to', 'long': 'I bring together, collect; I am profitable to.'}
{'brief': 'I help, benefit, do good', 'long': 'I help, benefit, do good, am useful (to), profit.'}
{'brief': 'I gain, win, avoid loss', 'long': 'I gain, acquire, win (over), avoid loss.'}
{'brief': 'I gain by business', 'long': 'I gain by business (trading).'}
{'brief': 'working, activity, trade, performance', 'long': 'working, activity, work, service, trade, business, gains of business, performance, practice.'}
{'brief': 'usefulness, profit, advantage', 'long': 'usefulness, profit, advantage, benefit, gain.'}
{'brief': 'I assent to', 'long': 'I assent to, consent, confess, agree with.'}
{'brief': 'advantage, gain, profit', 'long': 'advantage, gain, profit, help.'}
{'brief': 'gain, advantage', 'long': 'gain, advantage, profit.'}
{'brief': 'profitable, beneficial, useful', 'long': 'profitable, beneficial, useful.'}
{'brief': 'useful, profitable', 'long': 'useful, profitable.'}
{'brief': 'I help, profit, have joy of', 'long': 'I profit, benefit, help; mid: I have profit, derive benefit.'}
{'brief': 'a prostitute', 'long': 'a prostitute; met: an idolatrous community.'}
{'brief': 'chastisement, punishment', 'long': 'chastisement, punishment, torment, perhaps with the idea of deprivation.'}
{'brief': 'I chastise, punish', 'long': 'I chastise, curtail, punish; mid: I cause to be punished.'}
{'brief': 'I punish', 'long': 'I punish, avenge myself on.'}
{'brief': 'punishment', 'long': 'punishment, penalty.'}
{'brief': 'punishment, penalty', 'long': 'punishment, penalty.'}

{'brief': 'justice, judicial hearing, punishment', 'long': '(a) (originally: custom, usage) right, justice, (b) process of law, judicial hearing, (c) execution of sentence, punishment, penalty, (d) justice, vengeance.'}
{'brief': 'a queen', 'long': 'a queen.'}
{'brief': 'I extinguish, suppress', 'long': '(a) I extinguish, quench, (b) I suppress, thwart.'}
{'brief': 'I wake, arouse, raise up', 'long': '(a) I wake, arouse, (b) I raise up.'}

{'brief': 'I raise up, rise up', 'long': '(a) in trans. tenses: I raise up, cause to grow, (b) in intrans. tenses: I rise up from.'}
{'brief': 'I rise up against', 'long': 'intrans. tenses: I rise up against.'}
{'brief': 'I make to rise, I rise, shine', 'long': 'I make to rise, I rise, shine (generally of the sun, and hence met.).'}
{'brief': 'a rising again, resurrection', 'long': 'a rising again, resurrection.'}
{'brief': 'I wake out of sleep, I arouse', 'long': 'I wake out of sleep, arouse in general, stir up.'}
{'brief': 'I raise up, arouse', 'long': 'I raise up, arouse.'}
{'brief': 'I raise along with', 'long': 'I raise along with.'}
{'brief': 'I rebuke, chide, admonish, warn', 'long': '(a) I rebuke, chide, admonish, (b) I warn.'}
{'brief': 'I rebuke, expose', 'long': '(a) I reprove, rebuke, discipline, (b) I expose, show to be guilty.'}
{'brief': 'I rebuke, chide, reprove', 'long': 'I rebuke, chide, reprove, strike at.'}
{'brief': 'rebuke, reproof, refutation', 'long': 'rebuke, reproof, refutation.'}
{'brief': 'I receive, take', 'long': '(a) I receive, get, (b) I take, lay hold of.'}
{'brief': 'I take, receive, accept, welcome', 'long': 'I take, receive, accept, welcome.'}
{'brief': 'I make room, go, receive', 'long': '(lit: I make room, hence) (a) I have room for, receive, contain, (b) I make room for by departing, go, make progress, turn myself.'}

{'brief': 'I bring, receive, recover', 'long': '(a) act: I convey, bring, carry, (b) mid: I receive back, receive what has belonged to myself but has been lost, or else promised but kept back, or: I get what has come to be my own by earning, recover.'}
{'brief': 'I receive, accept, acknowledge', 'long': 'I receive, accept, acknowledge.'}
{'brief': 'I take, receive', 'long': 'I take from, receive from, or: I take to, receive (apparently not used of money), admit, acknowledge; I take with me.'}
{'brief': 'I get back, receive back', 'long': '(a) I get back, receive back, (b) I get (receive) as due (deserved), (c) mid: I draw aside, separate.'}
{'brief': 'I receive, welcome, entertain', 'long': 'I receive, welcome, entertain (with hospitality), embrace.'}
{'brief': 'I receive as a guest', 'long': 'I receive as a guest, entertain hospitably, welcome.'}
{'brief': 'I expect, welcome, accept', 'long': '(a) I await, expect, (b) I receive, welcome (originally: to my house), (c) I accept.'}
{'brief': 'I take to myself, welcome', 'long': '(a) I take to myself, (b) I take aside, (c) I welcome.'}
{'brief': 'I welcome, receive kindly, undertake', 'long': 'I welcome, receive kindly; I undertake, assume the responsibility of.'}
{'brief': 'I welcome in', 'long': 'I welcome in, admit, receive.'}
{'brief': 'I share in, partake of', 'long': '(a) with gen: I take a share (part) of, share in, partake of, (b) with acc: I take after (later) or take instead.'}
{'brief': 'I ordain, enact', 'long': '(a) I ordain, lay down, give the sanction of law to, enact, (b) I base legally, regulate, direct.'}
{'brief': 'I take up, receive, answer, suppose, welcome', 'long': '(a) I take up, (b) I welcome, entertain, (c) I answer, (d) I suppose, imagine.'}
{'brief': 'I accept, admit, welcome', 'long': 'I accept, admit, welcome.'}
{'brief': 'a reed, reed-pen', 'long': 'a reed; a reed-pen, reed-staff, measuring rod.'}
{'brief': 'red', 'long': 'red.'}
{'brief': 'rule, authority', 'long': 'rule, authority, sovereignty; a reign.'}
{'brief': 'I reign together with', 'long': 'I reign together with.'}
{'brief': 'I reject after testing, I disqualify', 'long': 'I reject after testing (examination), disqualify.'}
{'brief': 'I annul', 'long': 'I annul, make of no effect, set aside, ignore, slight; I break faith with.'}
{'brief': 'I ignore, despise', 'long': 'I set at naught, ignore, despise.'}
{'brief': 'I push or thrust away, reject', 'long': 'I push (thrust) away, repulse, reject, refuse.'}
{'brief': 'I deny, repudiate', 'long': '(a) I deny (a statement), (b) I repudiate (a person, or belief).'}
{'brief': 'a casting away, rejection, loss', 'long': 'a casting away, rejection, a loss.'}
{'brief': 'I spit upon, disdain, reject, loathe', 'long': 'I spit out, disdain, reject, loathe.'}
{'brief': 'worthy to be cast away, worthless', 'long': 'worthy to be cast away, worthless, regarded as vile.'}
{'brief': 'I make excuse, refuse, reject', 'long': 'I beg off, make excuse, deprecate, refuse, reject, decline, shun, avoid.'}
{'brief': 'a report, fame', 'long': 'a report, fame, saying.'}
{'brief': 'I make clear, explain', 'long': 'I make clear, explain fully.'}
{'brief': 'a word, speech, divine utterance, analogy', 'long': 'a word, speech, divine utterance, analogy.'}
{'brief': 'hearing, faculty of hearing, ear', 'long': 'hearing, faculty of hearing, ear; report, rumor.'}
{'brief': 'I relate in full, describe', 'long': 'I relate in full, describe, narrate.'}
{'brief': 'a sound, rumor', 'long': '(a) a sound, noise, (b) a rumor, report.'}
{'brief': 'I reveal, inform', 'long': '(a) I reveal, make known (in a law court), I lay information, inform, (b) I make known, point out.'}
{'brief': 'a message', 'long': 'a message.'}
{'brief': 'I explain, make declaration', 'long': 'I lead, show the way; met: I unfold, narrate, declare.'}
{'brief': 'report, tidings', 'long': 'report, tidings, information.'}
{'brief': 'I make visible, report against, appear before', 'long': 'I make visible (manifest); hence: I report (inform) against; pass: I appear before.'}
{'brief': 'I hear, listen', 'long': 'I hear, listen, comprehend by hearing; pass: is heard, reported.'}
{'brief': 'rest, cessation from labor, refreshment', 'long': 'rest, cessation from labor, refreshment.'}
{'brief': 'left, left behind, the remainder', 'long': 'left, left behind, the remainder, the rest, the others.'}
{'brief': 'I make to rest, give rest to, rest, take my ease', 'long': 'I make to rest, give rest to; mid. and pass: I rest, take my ease.'}
{'brief': 'I rest, am silent, live quietly', 'long': 'I rest from work, cease from altercation, am silent, live quietly.'}
{'brief': 'resting, rest', 'long': '(in the Old Testament of the rest attained by the settlement in Canaan), resting, rest, dwelling, habitation.'}
{'brief': 'relief, remission, indulgence, freedom, rest', 'long': 'relief, remission, indulgence, freedom, rest.'}
{'brief': 'I rest, cause to rest', 'long': '(a) trans: I cause to rest, bring to rest; I cause to refrain, (b) intrans: I rest.'}
{'brief': 'I return', 'long': 'I bend or turn back; I return.'}
{'brief': 'I turn back to', 'long': '(a) trans: I turn (back) to (towards), (b) intrans: I turn (back) (to [towards]); I come to myself.'}
{'brief': 'I put out, go up', 'long': '(a) nautical: I put out (from the shore), (lit: I take up a ship on to the high seas), (b) I go up, possibly: I go up again, return.'}
{'brief': 'I turn, am converted, change', 'long': 'I turn, am converted, change, change my direction.'}
{'brief': 'I turn back, return', 'long': 'I turn back, return.'}
{'brief': 'I return, come back again', 'long': 'I return, come back again.'}
{'brief': 'I depart, return', 'long': 'I unloose, unloose for departure, depart, return.'}

{'brief': 'I overturn, turn upside down, return, mid. and pass: I conduct myself, live', 'long': 'I overturn; I turn back, return; I turn hither and thither; pass: I turn myself about; I sojourn, dwell; I conduct myself, behave, live.'}
{'brief': 'wages, reward', 'long': '(a) pay, wages, salary, (b) reward, recompense, punishment.'}
{'brief': 'I give back, return, sell', 'long': '(a) I give back, return, restore, (b) I give, render, as due, (c) mid: I sell.'}
{'brief': 'a reward, recompense', 'long': 'a reward, recompense, retribution.'}
{'brief': 'reward, due punishment', 'long': '(lit: repayment of price or payment of price due), reward, due punishment.'}
{'brief': 'a short cloak', 'long': 'a short cloak, worn by military officers and soldiers.'}
{'brief': 'a wrapper, mantle, veil', 'long': 'a wrapper, mantle, veil, cloak, covering.'}
{'brief': 'a ruler, prince, leader', 'long': 'a ruler, governor, leader, leading man; with the Jews, an official member (a member of the executive) of the assembly of elders.'}
{'brief': 'I reign, rule', 'long': 'I reign, rule.'}
{'brief': 'a ruler, potentate', 'long': '(lit: a man who rules by force), a ruler, potentate; also: courtier, member of the court.'}
{'brief': 'ruler, beginning', 'long': '(a) rule (kingly or magisterial), (b) plur: in a quasi-personal sense, almost: rulers, magistrates, (c) beginning.'}
{'brief': 'I have authority, rule over', 'long': 'I have authority, rule over.'}
{'brief': 'rule, regulation, province', 'long': '(lit: a level, ruler), a rule, regulation, rule of conduct or doctrine, (b) a measured (defined) area, province.'}
{'brief': 'I rule, arbitrate', 'long': '(lit: to act as arbiter in the games), I rule, arbitrate.'}
{'brief': 'sack-cloth', 'long': 'sack-cloth, a sign of mourning.'}
{'brief': 'a sacrifice', 'long': 'abstr. and concr: sacrifice; a sacrifice, offering.'}
